The paper deals with visual question answering, which involves computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses a memory-augmented neural network, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves attention mechanisms, which is a common topic in cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper uses neural networks, which is a broad topic that can fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
